  message: <<EOM
You installed coronapoker: Poker game implemented in Java.

================================================================

  GPL COMPLIANCE AND SECURITY NOTICE
  
  This port has been patched for GPL compliance and security.

  ISSUE: Binary Downloads Disabled
  ================================
  CoronaPoker includes Panoptes, a closed-source cryptographic
  anti-cheat engine, which this port previously attempted to:
  
    • Download at runtime from GitHub (untrusted binary source)
    • Cache locally to ~/.coronapoker/Panoptes/
    • Load via JNI as native code

  This violates the GPLv3 license under which CoronaPoker is
  licensed, as it requires source code availability.

  APPLIED FIX
  ===========
  This port has been patched to:
  
    • DISABLE remote binary downloads
    • PREVENT native library loading on all platforms
    • RUN in pure-Java mode without cryptographic anti-cheat

  FUNCTIONAL LIMITATIONS
  ======================
  Without the Panoptes engine, the game will:
  
    • Have NO tamper detection
    • Have NO action blockchain verification
    • Have NO post-game auditing capabilities
    • Rely solely on Java-level game logic enforcement

  SECURITY IMPLICATIONS
  ======================
  • No untrusted binaries will be downloaded
  • No closed-source libraries will be executed
  • Game integrity depends on player honesty
  • Suitable for casual/trusted gameplay only

  For more information about this issue:
  https://github.com/tonikelope/coronapoker/issues/7

================================================================
EOM
}
